features: OVER THE SINK DRYING RACK: Fits neatly over most standard sized kitchen sinks. Measures 17” L X 12.5” W. Allows your kitchenware to air-dry while excess water drips conveniently right back into the sink.

KITCHEN SPACE SAVER: This rollable kitchen drying rack is easy to store out of the way when not in use. The over the sink, rollable design frees up your counter space from the traditional dish drainer.
PREMIUM QUALITY: Made with heat resistant heavy-duty silicon, with a gray finish. Looks great and withstands heavy usage.
MULTI-PURPOSE: This dish drainer also works as a non-slip trivet mat for hot pots and pans. Additionally useful for rinsing and air-drying fruits, vegetables and herbs.
EASY TO CLEAN: Lays flat to easily wipe down and keep looking clean and fresh. Keeps your kitchen organized, clean and tidy.
body.description: SAVES VALUABLE COUNTER SPACE This dish drying rack sits right over your sink, replacing the traditional bulky dish drainers that waste valuable counter space. Dishes or produce can drip right into your sink, rather than make a wet mess all over the counter. Excellent for apartment and RV kitchens, or anywhere your space is valuable. EASY STORAGE Roll or fold the drying rack when not in use and neatly place in a drawer, tuck behind the faucet or store in a cabinet, wherever you like. Conveniently designed to take up minimal storage space. MULTI-FUNCTIONAL Ideal for air drying kitchenware such as dishes, cups, and bowls and for drying fruits, vegetables or herbs. Also works great as a trivet for hot pots, pans and bakeware.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Portable, Useful and Easy to Clean
reviews.reviewText: The headline says it all. We recently installed an undermount cast iron sink with granite counters. During the same project we removed a stainless steel sink that had a drying rack as part of the sink. It was while using the former rack that I liked the functionality of it and purchased this rack. This rack is of much better quality than the one we got rid of. Only word of caution--Please measure your opening as our rack just barely rests over the sink opening. This product is well made and a good price.
